  "blurb": "An eight-bedroom villa in the gated Cape Amarin community on Kamala's Millionaire's Mile, spread across three levels of living with an infinity pool above the Andaman Sea. Fitness room, games area, bar, library and elevator sit within some 2,500 m², with a five-strong team and a private chef, sleeping up to sixteen.",
  "detail": "Within the gated Cape Amarin community on Kamala's Millionaire's Mile, this eight-bedroom villa spreads across three levels above the Andaman Sea. Traditional Thai architecture is threaded with contemporary lines, and the sea and surrounding foliage stay in view from the main living spaces.\n\nAn infinity pool reaches toward the horizon, with a shallow children's pool alongside and a broad lawn beyond. Two masters and six guest bedrooms, all en-suite, sleep up to sixteen across roughly 2,500 m², served by an elevator between floors.\n\nThe house is built for a group at play — a fitness room, an entertainment and games area with billiards and a ping-pong table, a bar, a mini library, a large-screen television and a sound system throughout. Dining runs Western or Japanese-style, and a backup generator keeps everything running.\n\nA team of five, including a private chef, looks after the day-to-day, with housekeeping, turndown, airport transfers and 24-hour estate security included; car hire, spa treatments, laundry and event planning are arranged on request. Kamala's beach and restaurants are a short drive down the hill.",
